/bin/
/node_modules/
/sdks/
# Stack config files are gitignored by default (they can hold passphrase-encrypted
# secrets). Pulumi.prod.yaml is the exception: its secrets are encrypted with
# Pulumi Cloud's managed KMS key (mt#2738), so the ciphertext is safe to commit —
# and CI needs it to run `pulumi preview`. See docs/deploy-minsky-railway.md.
Pulumi.*.yaml
!Pulumi.prod.yaml
